{
  "stem": "20848.2",
  "chunk_idx": 10,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 3.5,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, one day the Germans came, and they closed up the whole house and they took everybody from the, from the apartments onto the courtyard.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And we were put-- I don't remember how we were put, but we were standing all there.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And then, you see, the Germans first, when they were cleaning up the ghetto-- when I was cleaning up the ghetto is a terrible expression, but that's exactly what they were doing-- they, they, they first, they took people off the street that were homeless and, and, and people who were very poor and you know, beggars who, probably before the war, were very cultured people.",
      "word_count": 66
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "But during, due to the circumstances, they were reduced to being beggars.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And they straight away took them away.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "They must have killed them straight away.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And then they started with orphanages.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And that orphanage, when they took us down in the courtyard, they put those children in pairs.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And that day, they took out a lot of people from the courtyard that were there.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And they took the orphanage, the children were marching, put in pairs.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And Korczak, Dr.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "Korczak was standing next to the first pair.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And on the other side was standing a, a woman.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "I think that the woman was a, a teacher or, or, or a person who was employed there to look after the children.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "And later on, I found out-- I just saw them marching out.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "And I saw Korczak picking up a child and putting him like that and marching out of, of the, of the courtyard.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "And I didn't know it at the time, but later on I found out that he was allowed to stay.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "Apparently, the SS, the Germans, said to him, you don't have to go with the orphanage.",
      "word_count": 16
    }
  ],
